---
import Shell from '../layouts/Shell.astro';

const tokens: [string, string][] = [
  ['medium', 'markdown ledger'],
  ['rule', 'no design repeats'],
  ['entries', 'append-only'],
  ['repo', 'mtmattei/design-ledger'],
];
---
<Shell title="Ledger" crumb="ledger" tokens={tokens}
  description="design-ledger — a public, append-only record of design DNA that mechanically guarantees no generated interface repeats a previous one.">
  <div class="page-head">
    <span class="kicker">Skills · public record</span>
    <h1 class="title">Ledger</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      design-ledger is a public, append-only record of design DNA. Every generated interface
      writes its fingerprint before it ships; the next one must prove distance from every
      prior entry. Taste enforced mechanically, not remembered.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="specimen" style="border-top:1px solid var(--line)">
    <div><h3>What an entry records</h3><p>Palette DNA, type pairing, layout genome, and the one signature interaction — enough to detect a repeat, small enough to diff by eye.</p></div>
    <div class="read">4 fields · plain markdown</div>
  </div>
  <div class="specimen">
    <div><h3>The rule</h3><p>A new design must differ from every ledger entry across the recorded axes. Similar is allowed once it is declared; identical is a build failure of taste.</p></div>
    <div class="read">distance · not vibes</div>
  </div>
  <div class="specimen">
    <div><h3>Proof of work</h3><p>The Hollowpoint proof shipped as the first public demonstration: one prompt, one ledger, visibly divergent outputs.</p></div>
    <div class="read">hollowpoint · 2026-06</div>
  </div>
  <div class="specimen">
    <div><h3><a class="link-inline" href="https://github.com/mtmattei/design-ledger" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/mtmattei/design-ledger</a></h3><p>Open source. Bring your own agent; the ledger does not care which one.</p></div>
    <div class="read">public · OSS</div>
  </div>

  <p class="annotate" style="margin-top:var(--s6)"><span class="q">Question:</span> can aesthetic non-repetition be enforced by append-only history?</p>
</Shell>
